<h2>{% trans %}What this module provides{% endtrans %}</h2>
<p>{% trans %}BM Knowledge AI is a headless knowledge layer that normalizes disparate sources into KnowledgeItems, aggregates them via adapters, and attaches taxonomy/context metadata for AI-safe consumption.{% endtrans %}</p>

<h3>{% trans %}Core capabilities{% endtrans %}</h3>
<ul>
  <li>{% trans %}Canonical KnowledgeItem model with taxonomy, context hints, and authority level.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Adapter contract so sources like help topics, nodes, or documents can be added without changing consumers.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Classification service that reuses existing vocabularies for term attachment and filtering.{% endtrans %}</li>
  <li>{% trans %}Context and relevance services prepared for future AI ranking while remaining deterministic today.{% endtrans %}</li>
</ul>

<h3>{% trans %}Current consumer{% endtrans %}</h3>
<p>{% trans %}The bm_help_ai module registers a HelpKnowledgeAdapter to expose help topics and legacy hook_help entries through this layer, keeping its UI unchanged while sharing infrastructure.{% endtrans %}</p>

